Pumice.  Pretend I just repeated that ad nauseaum as well.<br>
<br>
The worst thing that can happen to a rogue in PvP is if somebody successfully roots or snares you.  The most you can hope to do to the caster with throwing weapons or archery is perhaps interrupt a few spells.<br>
<br>
From my experience on Tallon Zek, I've seen that most of the time monks and warriors won't mess with a rogue.  Casters who have some sort of root/snare ability love to pick on rogues, however.  If you can resist their root/snare, you can do a lot of damage to them.  They all rely on never letting you within melee distance, and I believe all the spells that do that are magic based.<br>
<br>
Disease resistances is pretty nice to have for tangling with necros and shamans.  As a rogue, you get some built in poison resistance.  But magic resist is the most important.  Much more important than armor class.  Get used to carrying two sets of armor, when you get a collection going.  Always wear your magic resist, and when you settle down at a camp to fight, then switch to the AC armor.   <br>
<br>
